addUnits(string[],uint256[]).details: Even though function is opened, it can be called only by world asset

params.unitsCount: Amounts of units will be added to siege
params.unitsNames: Unit types which will be added to siege

calculateArmySiegeStats(address).details: Values are calculated for specified army that is present in siege

calculateTotalSiegeStats().details: Values are calculated for all armies that are present in siege

returns._power: Total power that placed into siege

canLiquidate(address).details: Does not take into an account if army's battle is finished and army isn't left the battle

returns._0: Can army be liquidated from current siege

claimResources(address,uint256).details: Even though function is opened, it can be called only by world asset

params.points: Amount of points to spend for robbing

epoch().details: Value is dereferenced from proxy storage and world

getStoredUnits(address).details: Function returns only amounts without types, index in returned array for each unit type is same as in 'registry.getUnits'

returns.res: Amount of units that army has in siege

params.period: Time period to use to calculate damage

returns._0: Total damage for provided period of time

getUserPointsOnTime(address,uint256).details: If timestamp=0, returns value as if timestamp=block.timestamp

returns._0: Amount of points army will have at specified time

init(address).details: Called by factory contract which creates current instance

liquidate(address).details: Can be called by anyone, caller will receive a reward

systemUpdate(uint256).details: Even though function is opened, it can be called only by world asset

update().details: Synchronizes health up to current state, produces points for besieging armies

withdrawUnits(string[],uint256[]).details: Even though function is opened, it can be called only by world asset

params.unitsCount: Amounts of units will be withdrawn to siege
params.unitsNames: Unit types which will be withdrawn to siege

world().details: Value is dereferenced from proxy storage

currentSettlement.details: Immutable, initialized on the siege creation

lastUpdate.details: Updated when siege parameters related to pointsPerShare were changed

pointsPerShare.details: Updated when siege parameters related to armies were changed

Liquidated(address,string,uint256).notice: Emitted when #liquidate is called, emitted for every unit type that was liquidated

PointsReceived(address,uint256).notice: Emitted when #addUnits or #withdrawUnits is called in order to preserve previous amount of points were farmed by the army with previous speed

armyInfo(address).notice: Mapping containing army information related to current siege

canLiquidate(address).notice: Calculates if provided army address can be liquidated from current siege

claimResources(address,uint256).notice: Claims resources for specified points from building related to siege

currentSettlement().notice: Settlement address to which this siege belongs

getStoredUnits(address).notice: Returns amount of stored units for specified army in siege

getTotalDamageByPeriod(uint256).notice: Calculates total damage for provided period of time

getTotalDamageLastPeriod().notice: Calculates total damage for period from lastUpdate and block.timestamp

getUserPoints(address).notice: Calculates amount of points army has

getUserPointsOnTime(address,uint256).notice: Calculates amount of points army will have at specified time

lastUpdate().notice: Last time at which siege was updated

storedUnits(address,string).notice: Mapping containing amount of stored units in siege for specified army

systemUpdate(uint256).notice: Updates siege with new amount of damage fort taken

update().notice: Updates current siege to the current state
